{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "lib/request.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "test/req.host.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "History.md"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The deprecated req.host property is referenced in three source files within the sg-evals/expressjs-express repository. (1) lib/request.js (lines 452-456) defines the deprecated req.host property using the depd deprecation module. The property is a getter that returns this.hostname with a deprecation message 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. A TODO comment on line 452 indicates plans to change req.host behavior in a future major version. (2) test/req.host.js contains the test suite for the deprecated req.host property, with multiple test cases covering: basic Host header handling (lines 8-19), port number stripping (lines 21-32), undefined handling when headers.host is null (lines 34-45), IPv6 literal support (lines 47-71), and proxy behavior with 'trust proxy' enabled/disabled (lines 73-154). (3) History.md contains changelog entries documenting the deprecation and related fixes: line 1286 explicitly states 'deprecate req.host -- use req.hostname instead' in the 4.3.0 release notes; line 1284 documents the introduction of req.hostname as 'the correct name for what req.host returns'; line 1436 mentions 'fix req.host for IPv6 literals' in version 4.1.2; and line 2726 notes when req.host was originally 'Added' to Express. These files collectively define, test, and document the deprecated req.host property that was superseded by req.hostname."
}

